programme.title: Boys Town
programme.desc: A fact-based portrait of Father Edward J. Flanagan, a crusading priest who built a Nebraska community for orphans and believed that "there's no such thing as a bad boy," although his theory is sorely tested by a punky street tough who learns the hard way about the school's altruistic mission. Spencer Tracy's portrayal of the famous founding father won him his second consecutive Oscar (the first was for "Captains Courageous"). Best Picture nominee.

programme.title: Rebel Without a Cause
programme.desc: Inarticulate teenage alienation, rebelliousness and torment break out in violence in this character study about a sullen youth (James Dean) who moves with his parents to a well-to-do Los Angeles suburb, where he finds love, friendship and new enemies.

programme.title: 4 for Texas
programme.desc: Dean Martin and Frank Sinatra star as friendly enemies who both want to control gambling in 1870 Galveston, but first must contend with a crooked banker and cold-blooded hired gun.

programme.title: Woman of the Year
programme.desc: A Spencer Tracy-Katharine Hepburn battle of the sexes develops when her international-affairs columnist suggests to his flinty sportswriter that baseball be canceled for the duration of World War II. This was their first of nine screen pairings and Hepburn was nominated for Best Actress. Michael Kanin and Ring Lardner Jr.'s script won a Best Original Screenplay Oscar.

programme.title: Annie Hall
programme.desc: Woody Allen cowrote and directed this Best Picture, and stars as a neurotic Jewish comedian and writer recounting the roller-coaster relationship he had with a kooky, WASPish aspiring singer. The film employs fantasy flashbacks, direct-to-camera monologues, subtitles and even a cartoon sequence to tell its tale.

programme.title: Thieves' Highway
programme.desc: First-rate thriller about fruit truckers and racketeers. Richard Conte. Rica: Valentina Cortesa. Figlia: Lee J. Cobb. Polly: Barbara Lawrence. Ed: Millard Mitchell. Slob: Jack Oakie. Pete: Joseph Pevney. Excellent direction by Jules Dassin. Suspenseful and absorbing.

programme.title: The Natural
programme.desc: A middle-aged rookie takes the baseball world by storm with his self-made bat. He just might be able to use to his legendary talent to help the fictional New York Knights win the pennant. Adaptation of Bernard Malamud's 1952 novel.

programme.title: Dr. Strangelove Or: How I Learned to Stop Worrying and Love the Bomb
programme.desc: A fanatical U.S. general launches a nuclear attack on Russia during the Cold War, but the President and his advisors are shocked to learn that the Russians have technology that will destroy the world in the event of an attack on them.

programme.title: Madame Bovary
programme.desc: Flaubert's classic about a housewife's romantic longings and her affairs after becoming bored with her husband.

programme.title: Bus Stop
programme.desc: Adaptation of the William Inge play about a pathetic saloon singer who takes off for L.A. but is pursued by a lovesick Montana cowboy, who kidnaps her to bring her back to his hometown. As the cowboy, Don Murray was nominated for a Best Supporting Actor Oscar.

programme.title: Thieves' Highway
programme.desc: First-rate thriller about fruit truckers and racketeers. Richard Conte. Rica: Valentina Cortesa. Figlia: Lee J. Cobb. Polly: Barbara Lawrence. Ed: Millard Mitchell. Slob: Jack Oakie. Pete: Joseph Pevney. Excellent direction by Jules Dassin. Suspenseful and absorbing.

programme.title: Stormy Weather
programme.desc: Two lovers, one a tap dancer and the other a vocalist, split after each skyrockets to fame. They reunite at a musical stage show which showcases the talents of many of the popular African American performers of the 1940s.

programme.title: Jazz on a Summer's Day
programme.desc: Bert Stern's record of the 1958 Newport Jazz Festival. Louis Armstrong, Mahalia Jackson, Gerry Mulligan, Dinah Washington, George Shearing, Chico Hamilton, Jack Teagarden, Anita O'Day, Jimmu Giuffre, Thelonious Monk, Chuck Berry, Sal Salvadore. Songs include "Tea for Two," "All of Me," "Lazy River," "Tiger Rag," "Catch as Catch Can" and "The Lord's Prayer."

programme.title: How They Got Over
programme.desc: This music documentary foregrounds the often-overlooked legacy of the African-American gospel quartets of the Deep South and their foundational influence on the subsequent genres of rock and roll, doo-wop, rhythm and blues, soul and Motown. It features interviews with surviving members of the Dixie Hummingbirds, The Fairfield Four and The Heavenly Gospel Singers, as well as with Otis Clay and Dennis Edwards.

programme.title: The Wiz
programme.desc: A young kindergarten teacher finds herself in the Land of Oz, where she is greeted by Munchkins. As she journeys down the Yellow Brick Road in search of the Wiz, she encounters a scarecrow, a tin man and a cowardly lion.

programme.title: Life With Father
programme.desc: An 1880s New York financier runs a tight ship, but his wife is really the captain, especially when she realizes that he is not baptized.

programme.title: The Courtship of Eddie's Father
programme.desc: A young son thinks it's about time for his widowed father to start dating again, but he's not happy about dad's choices in women. So the lad takes matters into his own hands and tries to fix up his father with the attractive next-door neighbor. The film spawned a popular TV series (1969-72).

programme.title: The General
programme.desc: One of Buster Keaton's best efforts, this film has been called "the last great comedy of the silent screen." It's a Civil War story, with Keaton as a Confederate train engineer in search of his train. A frantic chase involves Keaton on the trail of Union soldiers, who in turn chase him. The plot is based on a true incident.

programme.title: Eijanaika
programme.desc: The dramatization of a brief but critical moment in Japanese history when Japan emerged from two centuries of isolationism in the 1860s. This new regime proves more receptive to opening Japan up to trade from the West—particularly America.

programme.title: Henry Goes Arizona
programme.desc: A vaudevillian (Frank Morgan) inherits a debt-ridden ranch---and troubles with ranch-jumpers. Molly: Virginia Weidler. Judge: Guy Kibbee. Sheriff: Slim Summerville. Pleasant. Directed by Edwin L. Marin.

programme.title: Drum Beat
programme.desc: Set during the 1869 Modoc Indian uprising along the California-Oregon border, a veteran Indian scout with a close relationship with the tribe is sent to negotiate a peace pact, but must deal with a renegade warrior who honors no treaties.

programme.title: The Deadly Companions
programme.desc: A former Civil War sergeant seeks revenge against a Confederate soldier who tried to scalp him in battle. The pair end up planning a bank robbery together that leads to the death of a young boy. The sergeant feels guilty about this, and soon also finds himself in love with the boy's mother.

programme.title: Trail Guide

programme.desc: Two aging but freewheeling horse wranglers dreaming of better days and hoping to make enough money to retire enter their wild, stubborn roan, who has a taste for alcohol, in a bucking-bronco contest at a rodeo.
